# Turso Content Source

- Treat Turso as the source of truth for content and configurable site data.
- Store articles, videos, products, donation links, navigation, page records, disclaimers, external URLs, and site settings in Turso whenever they can be persisted there.
- Read runtime content through `src/db/queries.ts`.
- Keep `src/db/content.ts` limited to bootstrap seed data for first-time setup or intentional reseeding.
- Do not import `src/db/content.ts` from app routes or components.
- Avoid adding hardcoded content arrays, JSON files, Markdown files, filesystem reads, or component-level copy that would require future content edits in code.
- When new content-driven behavior needs data, add or extend a Turso-backed table or `site_settings` key first.
